instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The twin generates optimal trajectories via the Trajectory Generator Service, publishes them to the MQTT broker, and the Physical Crane Interface consumes them, converting them into servo motor commands for the TMC4671‑Eval controllers. The Continuous Validation Service compares the executed motion to a simulated reference and publishes alerts to the Grafana dashboard when deviation thresholds are exceeded. All command and state updates flow through the same MQTT broker."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "Services operate in continuous real‑time; sensor data are sampled and logged at every motion step (~10–20 ms per wheel update), while trajectory computations and validation checks run per commanded trajectory (typically 1–5 s). Exact rates are derived from the motor controller loop frequencies but are not explicitly specified in the documentation."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The twin architecture is structured in C4 containers: Database, MQTT broker, Dashboard on the physical side; on the digital side, Logic containers (Control Application, Logging Application, Trajectory Generator Service, Simulation Service, Continuous Validation Service). All are connected via MQTT messaging, the database stores telemetry, and the dashboard exposes real‑time visualization. The Physical Crane Interface acts as bridge between hardware and software."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The twin models and services cover all lifecycle phases: (a) Designed – CAD models (Autodesk Fusion 360) and kinematic models used during design; (b) Manufactured – Simulation models and control firmware deployed on the physical hardware; (c) Operated – Continuous logging, real‑time control, validation, and visualization during day‑to‑day operation."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Validation is performed by the Continuous Validation Service, which executes the same trajectory in simulation and measures Euclidean distance between simulated and actual trajectory positions; if the distance exceeds user‑defined thresholds, the system flags a fault. The approach relies on accurate kinematic modelling and synchronous sampling. Uncertainty sources include sensor noise from encoders and anemometer, motor latency, and actuator compliance. The lack of a dedicated physical simulator limits fidelity during development."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "Communication between PT and DT occurs over a local Ethernet network using MQTT (port 1883) for command and telemetry messages, and PostgreSQL/TimescaleDB (port 5432) for database storage. MQTT topics are used for trajectory commands, sensor telemetry, and validation alerts. The Physical Crane Interface and all services run on the same host PC, leveraging local TCP/IP."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The twin is deployed on a personal computer that also hosts the physical crane. All services are containerized with Docker; Docker Compose brings up TimescaleDB, Mosquitto, Grafana, and the twin application containers with a single command. The host therefore runs both robotic hardware and the digital twin pipeline in a unified environment."
]
